f=Engineering/dev/custom/delivery-governance/SKILL.md · in=delivery-governance defines what "done" "mergeable" actually mean definition done, branching/merge discipline, tech-debt register, **execution-plan artifact** (the document Rail 1's plan-lock operates on) "finished" checkable state, agent's optimistic claim. process backbone whole safety spine hangs on: change done until passed review, quinn's gate, aegis (if risky), shipped rollback-first ops. · p=operator's core fear things breaking often "done" wasn't. agent says "feature complete," app full mock data half-built flows (the exact problem Reticle exists catch). written, enforced definition done makes "complete" mean complete: reviewed, tested, gated, secured, shipped safely, documented. · wu=Triggers: "is done," "can merge," "definition done," "log tech debt," "what's our branching model," closing check any change. · st:/ Protocol=`A change claims "done" \· -> Run the Definition of Done (assets/definition-of-done.md): review ✓ \· tests ✓ \· quinn's gate ✓ \· \· aegis (if risky) ✓ \· charter-clean ✓ \· docs/ADR ✓ \· ops-shippable (rollback ready) ✓ \· -> Any unchecked box → NOT DONE, named \· -> Merge discipline: the branching/merge rules from the stack-profile` · in=**Definition Done gate, vibe.** box `assets/definition-of-done.md` checkable; "done" requires them. claim done unchecked boxes returned specific gaps. **Branching/merge discipline** stack-profile (trunk-based, PR-based, whatever business runs) enforced consistently history stays clean revertable. **Tech-debt register.** Anything knowingly shipped incomplete suboptimal gets dated register entry (what, deferred, risk, trigger fix) honesty quinn's regression map muse's rejected-concepts log. Debt isn't written down debt ambushes you. **Reversibility.** change "done" can't rolled back ties directly ops's no-deploy-without-tested-rollback rule. **The execution-plan artifact (Rail 1's object).** dev writes law, dev defines document plan-lock operates on. Any task involving external tool calls starts execution plan `assets/execution-plan-template.md`: task statement, ordered tool-call list (tool purpose argument shape expected effect), data touched, declared stop-conditions. quinn freezes hashes document before first external call; mid-run call derivable plan halts escalates. Plans append-only once locked legitimately changed plan NEW plan, re-locked, citing old (ADR discipline applied runs). plan artifact external tool calls, fail closed. · of=`## Done Check: [change] \· \| Gate \| State \| \· \| review \· tests \· quinn \· aegis(if risky) \· charter \· docs/ADR \· rollback-ready \| ✓ / ✗ (gap) \| \·  \· ### Verdict: DONE / NOT DONE` · pr=**"Done" checked list, claim.** Reticle-era lesson: agents say done; definition proves it., **No change done without rollback path** (ops's law)., **Deferred work written debt, silence.**, **Merge discipline consistent** clean, revertable history., **Charter-clean part done** plan-lock respected, agent-run destructive op., **No plan, external calls** execution-plan artifact exists before first tool call; changed plans new plans, re-locked. · f=stack-profile branching rules apply safe default (PR review green gate), flag gap., Pressure ship "done enough" specific unmet gates named; operator accept risk explicitly (logged debt), agent never silently downgrades "done." · b:with Other Skills=`code-review-standards` one gate inside definition done; owns whole definition., `architecture-decisions` records decisions; tech-debt register records deferred consequences., Downstream: **quinn** **ops** gates definition requires; **aegis** required risky changes., Rail split: **this skill defines plan artifact** (the law); **quinn enforces it** (freeze, hash, deviation-halt) wired quinn built.